  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mitigation of Negative Climate Change Impact and Fostering of Climate Smart Agriculture</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Myanmar&#x2019;s Ayerrawaddy region climate change is a major challenge for communities due to irregular or erratic rainfall, salt intrusion, floods and extreme temperatures that affect farmers as well as landless households. These negative impacts are exacerbated by the lack of knowledge on climate change and climate change adaption livelihoods, lack of environmental care education and practice, poor participation of community level governance structures, livelihoods that depend upon traditional agriculture techniques with high chemical fertilizers inputs and lack of community participation in advocacy processes. Moreover, in 2020 with the COVID 19 crisis communities are facing more difficulties related to food security, lack of income generating activities and health issues. Unemployment rates are growing, and farmers are losing their livelihood as movement restrictions have been imposed and limited their capacity to sell their products and be able to pay back their debts. 

In this sense KMSS Pathein will aim to support 20 villages so farmers and communities can lead positive change processes for environmental sustainability and creation of livelihood-based agriculture opportunities that contribute to mitigate the impact of climate change. In order to do this KMSS will integrate three main components: a) creation and empowerment (knowledge, skills and capacity building) of local governance structures (Village Development Committees VDC and Self Help groups SHG) to lead development processes in their own communities; b) promotion and practice of organic farming, as an adaptation strategy to climate change and variability; c) advocacy to local government in order to align development processes as well as establishment of networks with other local actors across the region for common agenda on sustainability.</narrative>
  </description>
